input.content:
# Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code

## Context

T3 Code currently has a minimal light/dark/system mode toggle (`useTheme` in `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) that works by toggling a `.dark` CSS class. The request adds a richer **named color theme system** — Theme definitions with full color palettes, font settings, and CSS custom property injection — backed by definitions in `packages/shared` and surfaced via a React hook and a UI component.

---

## Critical Design Decision: Hook Naming

The existing `useTheme()` hook (returns `{ theme, setTheme, resolvedTheme }`) is used in 5 files and controls dark/light/system mode via the `.dark` CSS class. The new requirement specifies a `useTheme()` hook with `{ theme, setTheme, availableThemes }` — a different shape.

**Decision**: Name the new hook `useColorTheme()` to avoid breaking the existing system. The two hooks coexist:
- `useTheme` → dark/light/system mode (CSS class)
- `useColorTheme` → named color palette (CSS custom properties)

This follows the project's existing pattern of preferring correctness and predictability.

---

## Files to Create

1. `packages/shared/src/themes.ts`
2. `apps/web/src/hooks/useColorTheme.ts`
3. `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`

## Files to Modify

4. `packages/shared/package.json` — add `./themes` subpath export
5. `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` — add "Color Theme" section
6. `apps/web/src/index.css` — add fallback CSS custom property declarations

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` (new file)

Follow the pattern of `git.ts` (pure functions, `readonly`, JSDoc, named exports, no default exports).

```typescript
export interface ThemeColors {
  readonly background: string;
  readonly foreground: string;
  readonly accent: string;
  readonly sidebar: string;
  readonly editor: string;
  readonly terminal: string;
  readonly statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly colors: ThemeColors;
  readonly fontFamily: string;
  readonly fontSize: number;
  /** Whether this theme uses a dark color scheme. Used to sync the `.dark` class. */
  readonly isDark: boolean;
}
```

Three built-in themes (concrete hex/oklch values, not CSS var references, so they work as inline style values):

| Theme ID | Name | isDark | Background | Accent |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `t3-dark` | T3 Dark | true | `#09090b` | `oklch(0.588 0.217 264)` |
| `t3-light` | T3 Light | false | `#ffffff` | `oklch(0.488 0.217 264)` |
| `t3-midnight` | T3 Midnight | true | `#0c0e1a` | `oklch(0.65 0.2 290)` |

Default theme ID constant: `"t3-dark"`.

Export two functions:
```typescript
export function getTheme(id: string): Theme | undefined { ... }
export function listThemes(): readonly Theme[] { ... }
```

---

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json` (modify)

Add one entry to the `"exports"` map:
```json
"./themes": {
  "types": "./src/themes.ts",
  "import": "./src/themes.ts"
}
```
This follows the exact pattern of every other entry (`./model`, `./git`, etc.).

---

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useColorTheme.ts` (new file)

Mirror the `useSyncExternalStore` pattern from `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` exactly.

Key elements:
- **Storage key**: `"t3code:color-theme"` (namespaced like all other keys)
- **Default theme ID**: `"t3-dark"`
- **`applyColorTheme(theme, suppressTransitions?)`**: Sets inline CSS custom properties on `document.documentElement` and syncs the `.dark` class:
  ```typescript
  root.style.setProperty("--background", theme.colors.background);
  root.style.setProperty("--foreground", theme.colors.foreground);
  root.style.setProperty("--card", theme.colors.background);
  root.style.setProperty("--popover", theme.colors.background);
  root.style.setProperty("--primary", theme.colors.accent);
  root.style.setProperty("--ring", theme.colors.accent);
  root.style.setProperty("--theme-sidebar", theme.colors.sidebar);
  root.style.setProperty("--theme-editor", theme.colors.editor);
  root.style.setProperty("--theme-terminal", theme.colors.terminal);
  root.style.setProperty("--theme-status-bar", theme.colors.statusBar);
  root.style.setProperty("--theme-font-family", theme.fontFamily);
  root.style.setProperty("--theme-font-size", `${theme.fontSize}px`);
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", theme.isDark);
  ```
  Inline style properties override `:root` CSS declarations (higher specificity), so the palette takes effect immediately regardless of the `.dark` class CSS rules.
- **Module-level `applyColorTheme` call** on load to prevent flash (same pattern as existing `useTheme`).
- **`subscribe`** listens for `storage` events on `STORAGE_KEY` for cross-tab sync.

```typescript
export function useColorTheme() {
  const themeId = useSyncExternalStore(subscribe, getSnapshot);
  const theme = getTheme(themeId) ?? getTheme(DEFAULT_THEME_ID)!;
  const availableThemes = listThemes();

  const setTheme = useCallback((id: string) => { ... }, []);

  useEffect(() => { applyColorTheme(theme); }, [theme]);

  return { theme, setTheme, availableThemes } as const;
}
```

---

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` (new file)

A self-contained component that uses `useColorTheme()`. Follow the radio group pattern already used in the "Appearance" section of `_chat.settings.tsx` (the existing `THEME_OPTIONS` button group).

Structure:
```tsx
<div role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color theme" className="space-y-2">
  {availableThemes.map((t) => (
    <button key={t.id} role="radio" aria-checked={active} onClick={() => setTheme(t.id)}
      className={`flex w-full items-center gap-3 rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 text-left transition-colors ${activeStyles}`}
    >
      {/* Three preview swatches: background, foreground, accent */}
      <div className="flex shrink-0 gap-1" aria-hidden="true">
        <span className="size-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10"
          style={{ background: t.colors.background }} />
        <span className="size-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10"
          style={{ background: t.colors.foreground }} />
        <span className="size-4 rounded-sm border border-white/10"
          style={{ background: t.colors.accent }} />
      </div>
      <span className="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">{t.name}</span>
